/*
    A demonstration program for GC BASIC
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    This program shows toggling an LED attached to a PIC18F16Q20

    Note:
        To make the PIC operate you will need to connect Pin8 ( VDDIO2/VDDIO5 ) to a VDD within specification ( 5v0 or 3v3 ) on specific ports
        SAF protection config is not operation by design.  The user will have to uncomment the SAF operation config in the chip specific DAT file. And, use PICKit4/5 to program

    @author    Evan R Venn   
    @license   GPL
    @version   1.00
    @date      04-02-2024
    ********************************************************************************
*/


#CHIP 18F16Q20, 32
#option Explicit

/*
    Hardware
    -------------------PORTA----------------
    Bit#:  -7---6---5---4---3---2---1---0---
    IO:    --------------------------------- 
    -----------------------------------------
    

    -------------------PORTB----------------
    Bit#:  -7---6---5---4---3---2---1---0---
    IO:    ---------------------------------
    -----------------------------------------
    
    ------------------PORTC-----------------
    Bit#:  -7---6---5---4---3---2---1---0---
    IO:    LED-LED-LED-LED------------------
    ----------------------------------------
*/

// *****************************************************************************************************
    // Main program commences here.. everything before this is setup for the board.

    DIR PORTC Out
    do

        // Set the LEDs on
        PORTC = 255
        wait 500 ms
        
        // Set the LEDs off
        PORTC = 0
        wait 500 ms

    loop


